&lt;/h2>&lt;p>we will use WordPress &lt;code>get_the_date()&lt;/code> Hook.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I will explain both. If you have created meta field for date &lt;code>post_custom_date&lt;/code>. OR using &lt;a class="link" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-custom-fields/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>ACF&lt;/a> created field with name &lt;code>post_custom_date&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="inspiration">Inspiration
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>When I was developing the site with &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.elegantthemes.com/gallery/divi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>Divi theme&lt;/a> there is a custom post listing module but I don&amp;rsquo;t want the date of publishing post instead i want my custom date which I have created with &lt;a class="link" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-custom-fields/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>ACF&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So I have searched and found this solution Enjoy. &amp;#x1f389;&lt;/p>
